<div class="page">

  <!-- ░░ HEADER ░░ -->
  <header class="header">
    <div class="header-top">
      <div class="header-meta">
        <span class="meta-issue">Issue No. 01</span>
        <span class="meta-date">Sunday, June 15, 2026 · Week 25</span>
      </div>
      <div class="header-refresh">
        <span class="refresh-ts">Refreshed Jun 15 at 1:00 pm</span>
        <button class="refresh-btn">↻ Refresh Now</button>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="masthead-wrap">
      <span class="greeting">Good Sunday, Jay.</span>
      <h1 class="masthead">The B-Side</h1>
      <div class="tagline-rule">
        <div class="tagline-line"></div>
        <span class="tagline-text">Sport &nbsp;·&nbsp; Music &nbsp;·&nbsp; Style &nbsp;·&nbsp; Culture</span>
        <div class="tagline-line"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- ░░ VIBE ░░ -->
  <div class="vibe">
    <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;opacity:0.75;">
    <span class="vibe-caption" style="position:relative;z-index:1;">— the week, distilled.</span>
  </div>

  <div class="body">

    <!-- ░░ THE HERO ░░ -->
    <div class="section">
      <span class="eyebrow">The Hero · This Week's Lead Story</span>
      <h2 class="section-hed">The World Cup Is Here. Everything Else Is Background Noise.</h2>
      <p class="body-text">The 2026 FIFA World Cup — the largest in football history at 48 teams — kicked off Thursday across the USA, Canada, and Mexico. The opening week delivered exactly what it promised: chaos, upsets, and a level of cultural saturation that makes the tournament feel less like sport and more like a shared global hallucination. Brazil drew Morocco 1-1 in a match that had the internet paralysed. Australia dismantled Turkey 2-0. Scotland — Scotland — beat Haiti 1-0 and collected their first-ever World Cup win. The group stage has barely begun and the discourse is already deafening.</p>
      <div class="why-matters">
        <span class="why-label">Why it matters</span>
        <p class="why-text">This tournament runs through mid-July and will define summer culture globally — anthems, kits, fan rituals, and the conversation at every gathering you attend. If you're not at least across the storylines, you'll be lost for the next six weeks.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="buzz-row">
        <span class="buzz-label">Buzz Meter</span>
        <div class="buzz-bar-track"><div class="buzz-bar-fill" style="width:100%"></div></div>
        <span class="buzz-score">10/10</span>
      </div>
      <div class="sources">
        <a class="source-link" href="https://sports.yahoo.com" target="_blank">Yahoo Sports · Jun 15, 2026</a>
        <span class="source-sep">·</span>
        <a class="source-link" href="https://www.sbs.com.au/news" target="_blank">SBS News · Jun 15, 2026</a>
        <span class="source-sep">·</span>
        <a class="source-link" href="https://olympics.com" target="_blank">Olympics.com · Jun 2026</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ░░ THE BUZZ ░░ -->
    <div class="section">
      <span class="eyebrow">The Buzz</span>
      <div class="buzz-grid">

        <div class="buzz-card">
          <span class="buzz-card-tag">Sport</span>
          <h3 class="buzz-card-hed">The Knicks Are Champions. New York Has Been Waiting 53 Years.</h3>
          <p class="buzz-card-body">On June 13, the New York Knicks beat the San Antonio Spurs 94–90 in Game 5 to win their first NBA title since 1973. Jalen Brunson scored 45 points — including 13 straight in the fourth quarter — and earned Finals MVP. Every game in the series was within 5 points in the final five minutes. The Knicks trailed in every game they won and came back in all four of them.</p>
          <div class="buzz-row">
            <span class="buzz-label">Buzz</span>
            <div class="buzz-bar-track"><div class="buzz-bar-fill" style="width:90%"></div></div>
            <span class="buzz-score">9/10</span>
          </div>
          <div class="sources">
            <a class="source-link" href="https://olympics.com" target="_blank">Olympics.com</a>
            <span class="source-sep">·</span>
