    <!-- ░░ TRENDING NOW ░░ -->
    <div class="section">
      <span class="eyebrow">Trending Now</span>
      <div class="trending-list">

        <div class="trending-item">
          <span class="trending-num">01</span>
          <h3 class="trending-hed">The World Cup Fan Culture Machine Is Running at Full Speed</h3>
          <p class="trending-body">Anthem audios, fan-zone content, kit discourse, and 'my country at the World Cup' formats have taken over TikTok and Instagram Reels. Josh Fawaz's remix is the default soundtrack across platforms right now.</p>
          <p class="trending-body">48 teams means more nations represented than any previous tournament. The sheer volume of fan communities generating content is creating micro-cultural moments that sports media isn't fully tracking but social absolutely is.</p>
          <a class="trending-source" href="https://buffer.com" target="_blank">↗ Buffer / TikTok Trends Jun 2026</a>
        </div>

        <div class="trending-item">
          <span class="trending-num">02</span>
          <h3 class="trending-hed">New York Is Having a Moment — and the Internet Has Opinions</h3>
          <p class="trending-body">The Knicks title plus Vulture Festival plus summer energy in the city is generating a wave of 'NYC is back' content, counterarguments, nostalgia, and discourse about what it actually means for a city to 'be back.'</p>
          <p class="trending-body">Every few years New York becomes the centre of the cultural conversation. It happened again this week, more concretely than usual.</p>
          <a class="trending-source" href="https://cbssports.com" target="_blank">↗ CBS Sports / Olympics.com</a>
        </div>

        <div class="trending-item">
          <span class="trending-num">03</span>
          <h3 class="trending-hed">Boards of Canada Reddit Is in Full Investigation Mode</h3>
          <p class="trending-body">r/boardsofcanada has been decoding <em>Inferno</em> track by track, hunting for ARG-style clues, and debating whether the album's title and a completed five-album Warp deal signal the end. Paste Magazine's 'air of finality' headline set the whole thing off.</p>
          <p class="trending-body">BOC has always cultivated obsessive listening communities. The 'is this the end?' energy is making non-fans curious in a way that no amount of traditional press coverage could.</p>
          <a class="trending-source" href="https://pastemagazine.com" target="_blank">↗ Paste Magazine</a>
        </div>

        <div class="trending-item">
          <span class="trending-num">04</span>
          <h3 class="trending-hed">Are 'Sports Maximalism' Collabs Becoming a Movement?</h3>
          <p class="trending-body">Adidas × Willy Chavarria and Marine Serre × Under Armour both dropped in the same window with a similar philosophical angle — high fashion reinterpreting athletic heritage through exaggerated proportion and craft. Fashion Twitter is debating whether this is a new aesthetic direction or two coincidences.</p>
          <p class="trending-body">When two independently conceived collabs land simultaneously with the same aesthetic thesis, it usually means something is shifting. Worth watching.</p>
          <a class="trending-source" href="https://highsnobiety.com" target="_blank">↗ Highsnobiety / Complex</a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

