    <!-- ░░ CONVERSATION STARTER ░░ -->
    <div class="section">
      <span class="eyebrow">Conversation Starter of the Week</span>
      <div class="convo-inner">
        <span class="convo-label">If someone brings up…</span>
        <div class="convo-topic">The Jalen Brunson MVP debate</div>
        <p class="convo-body">Brunson's 45-point game was the headline, but the real story is that every Knicks win this series required him to be historically clutch in the fourth quarter while playing 40-plus minutes a night — not once, but across four consecutive games. The interesting question isn't whether he deserved MVP (he did). It's: what does it mean that the Knicks had to trail every game to win it? That's the pattern. That's the team. Ask them that and see where it goes.</p>
